# Common Mistakes to Avoid

## ❌ Don't

### Content

- **Add sensitive internal information**
  - No internal architecture details
  - No business secrets
  - No customer data

- **Use absolute URLs for internal links**
  ```markdown
  ❌ [API docs](https://auditledger.github.io/api/overview.html)
  ✅ [API docs](../api/overview.md)
  ```

- **Skip language tags in code blocks**
  ```markdown
  ❌ ```
     code here
     ```

  ✅ ```python
     code here
     ```
  ```

- **Create pages without updating navigation**
  - Always add new pages to `mkdocs.yml` nav section
  - Test navigation structure

- **Commit without testing**
  - Must run `mkdocs build --strict` successfully
  - Preview changes locally first

### Formatting

- **Use title case for headings**
  ```markdown
  ❌ ## Getting Started With The SDK
  ✅ ## Getting started with the SDK
  ```

- **Use generic link text**
  ```markdown
  ❌ Click [here](../guide.md) for more info.
  ✅ See the [deployment guide](../guide.md) for details.
  ```

- **Hardcode credentials or keys**
  ```python
  ❌ client = Client(api_key="sk_live_123abc...")
  ✅ client = Client(api_key=os.getenv("AUDITLEDGER_API_KEY"))
  ```

### Workflow

- **Push broken builds**
  - CI/CD will fail
  - Blocks deployment

- **Ignore virtual environment**
  - Always activate: `source venv/bin/activate`
  - Keep dependencies in sync

- **Skip PR template**
  - Makes review harder
  - Missing context

## ✅ Do

### Content

- **Test all changes locally**
  ```bash
  ./start-mkdocs.sh restart
  mkdocs build --strict
  ```

- **Use relative links for internal docs**
  ```markdown
  [Getting started](../getting-started/overview.md)
  ```

- **Specify language in all code blocks**
  ```markdown
  ```python
  # Python code
  ```

  ```bash
  # Shell commands
  ```
  ```

- **Follow the style guide**
  - Sentence case headings
  - Active voice
  - Second person ("you")

- **Keep content public-appropriate**
  - Developer-focused
  - No internal details
  - Test examples work

### Workflow

- **Update navigation when adding pages**
  ```yaml
  nav:
    - New Section:
      - Overview: new-section/overview.md  # Add this
  ```

- **Test before committing**
  ```bash
  source venv/bin/activate
  mkdocs build --strict  # Must pass
  ```

- **Use the PR template**
  - Fill all sections
  - Check boxes
  - Add screenshots

### Quality

- **Add cross-references**
  - Link to related documentation
  - Help users navigate

- **Include working examples**
  - Test code before including
  - Add error handling
  - Use comments

- **Optimize images**
  - Compress before adding
  - Use appropriate formats
  - Keep files under 500KB

## Quick Checklist

Before committing, verify:

- [ ] `mkdocs build --strict` passes
- [ ] Changes previewed locally
- [ ] No sensitive information included
- [ ] Code blocks have language tags
- [ ] Links use relative paths (internal)
- [ ] Navigation updated (if new pages)
- [ ] Images optimized
- [ ] Writing follows style guide
- [ ] Virtual environment activated
